# Heroku Deployment Guide

## App Details
- **URL:** https://portugal2026-7f6200f7237c.herokuapp.com/
- **Platform:** Heroku
- **Buildpack:** Python (heroku/python)

---

## Prerequisites
1. Heroku CLI installed: `brew install heroku/brew/heroku`
2. Git repository initialized
3. Google OAuth credentials configured (see GOOGLE_OAUTH_SETUP.md)

---

## Initial Deployment

### 1. Login to Heroku
```bash
heroku login
```

### 2. Create Heroku App (if not already created)
```bash
heroku create portugal2026
```

### 3. Set Environment Variables
```bash
heroku config:set SECRET_KEY="<generate-with-openssl-rand-base64-32>"
heroku config:set GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID="<from-google-cloud-console>"
heroku config:set GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET="<from-google-cloud-console>"
heroku config:set ALLOWED_EMAILS="srinaths@gmail.com"
heroku config:set FLASK_ENV="production"
```

### 4. Update Google OAuth Redirect URI
**CRITICAL STEP** - Add to Google Cloud Console:
- Authorized redirect URI: `https://portugal2026-7f6200f7237c.herokuapp.com/auth/callback`
- Authorized JavaScript origin: `https://portugal2026-7f6200f7237c.herokuapp.com`

See GOOGLE_OAUTH_SETUP.md Step 7 for detailed instructions.

### 5. Deploy to Heroku
```bash
git push heroku main
```

### 6. View Logs
```bash
heroku logs --tail
```

---

## Updating the App

After making changes:
```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Your commit message"
git push heroku main
```

---

## Environment Variables Management

### View all config vars
```bash
heroku config
```

### Add a new allowed email
```bash
heroku config:set ALLOWED_EMAILS="srinaths@gmail.com,nirupa@example.com,darshan@example.com"
```

### Update SECRET_KEY for production
```bash
heroku config:set SECRET_KEY="$(openssl rand -base64 32)"
```

